user_message:
An agent A claimed that the following MHD_get_fdset code violates the MISRA C 2023 rule 17.2.
<misra_rule>
MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.2 is Functions shall not call themselves, either directly or indirectly.

</misra_rule>
<target_code>
Here is the original code of MHD_get_fdset.
```c
_MHD_EXTERN enum MHD_Result
MHD_get_fdset (struct MHD_Daemon *daemon,
               fd_set *read_fd_set,
               fd_set *write_fd_set,
               fd_set *except_fd_set,
               MHD_socket *max_fd)
{
  return MHD_get_fdset2 (daemon,
                         read_fd_set,
                         write_fd_set,
                         except_fd_set,
                         max_fd,
#ifdef HAS_FD_SETSIZE_OVERRIDABLE
                         daemon->fdset_size_set_by_app ?
                         ((unsigned int) daemon->fdset_size) :
                         ((unsigned int) _MHD_SYS_DEFAULT_FD_SETSIZE)
#else  /* ! HAS_FD_SETSIZE_OVERRIDABLE */
                         ((unsigned int) _MHD_SYS_DEFAULT_FD_SETSIZE)
#endif /* ! HAS_FD_SETSIZE_OVERRIDABLE */
                         );
}
```
</target_code>
